data.description: 20 base zoom (+4 over the others and +2 over Horror Story with Med scope) makes this best in class for range. Arrowhead + Rico + Killing Wind + MKC/HIR/KW + 68 range (=88 range) = 38m which beats 100 range 16 zooms by nearly 2M.

Despite Iron Reach greatly increasing the range, this gun has to stand up against the stat monster that is Palindrome. Even while fully statted into Range, it loses to Pali by 3m. While this might be an alternative for those who dislike the zoom that Rangefinder gives, it’s better off being used on an Arc Subclass with Elemental Capacitor for a huge Handling stat or relegated to the trash.

Frenzy is +50 to reload, so that perk alone puts Fatebringer at max reload speed. Loader will still add a scalar so it will be faster. Kill Clip does not boost Explosive Payload damage, just the impact damage. Explosive sometimes interferes with Firefly explosions.

Kill Clip does not improve TTK - just forgiveness and effective range. Opening Shot is still likely the best in slot, but do not sleep on Eye of the Storm for a mid-duel consistency boost, because of its mid-combat proc condition often occuring during 1v1 duels, the accuracy bump EotS grants could be excellent for finishing a fight.

Choosing between Reservoir Burst and HIR in PvE depends on the situation. HIR for boss damage and Reservoir Burst for general use and add clear. HIR is the clear winner for PvP, since it reduces the bolts needed for a kill while procced, and one stack of Heating Up makes the recoil perfectly vertical for easier bolt control.

A mediocre PvE archetype with solid enough perks.

A solid Precision shotgun for PvP, which is unfortunately overshadowed by the strength of the Matador. Run Smallbore and Accurized with a Range mw to maximize the range without dropping Handling. Unfortunately Precisions are struggling in the high resilience meta we find ourselves in, needing an extra pellet to kill on 6 resilience and higher.
